postcontent: Description / Manufacturer Information:  The Calico-series of firearms were produced around 1990 by the US company Calico Light Weapon Systems (LWS). The Calico’s are extremely abnormal in appearance and operation, mostly due to the helical-fed magazine system implemented. The cylinder atop the weapon is capable of carrying an astounding 100-9mm rounds. While boasting so much firepower, the weapon possessed a slim profile to the extent that some Calico models were able to be wielded as very small SMGs. The Calico designs were ambidextrous, semi-automatic or full-auto, and spent shells were ejected from below the firearm.
